Name: iliac vein thrombophlebitis
Definition: A degeneration of macula and posterior pole that is characterized by a loss of vision in the center of the visual field (the macula) resulting from damage to the retina and resulting in blurring of the sharp central vision.
Synonym: Phlebitis and thrombophlebitis of the iliac vein

Name: femoral vein thrombophlebitis
Definition: A pyoderma that is a milder form of diphtheria restricted to the skin producing shallow skin ulcers is caused by direct physical contact of indivduals infected with Corynebacterium diphtheriae as the bacteria releases the diphtheria toxin.

Name: obsolete maternal pyrexia in labor
Definition: A pyoderma that is a milder form of diphtheria restricted to the skin producing shallow skin ulcers is caused by direct physical contact of indivduals infected with Corynebacterium diphtheriae as the bacteria releases the diphtheria toxin.

Name: thrombophlebitis migrans
Definition: A thrombophlebitis that is characterized by repeated occurances of thrombophlebitis in different locations.
